data.description: Discover this splendid residence situated in a serene, countryside-like setting on 7 acres in Simpsonville, SC. This property allows for horses and boasts a custom-built, all-brick home that surpasses new construction standards. Impeccable renovations and upgrades have transformed this home into a masterpiece. The recent extensive improvements range from a complete kitchen overhaul, to the installation of a high-efficiency HVAC system (completed in 2020) that involved updating all ductwork and incorporating a whole-house ionic filtration system. New "Low-e" windows, a bonus sunroom, and a detached one-car workshop with electrical amenities are just a few highlights among many. The house is discreetly positioned at the end of a tranquil cul-de-sac, enveloped by a spacious front yard adorned with a welcoming fountain at the center of the circular driveway—a true embodiment of Southern charm. The kitchen seamlessly opens to the second-story living space, boasting a fluid design that's perfect for hosting gatherings. A stunning two-story stacked stone fireplace and a balcony enhance the ambiance, providing an enchanting canvas for holiday decorations. Premium-grade granite, including commercial-grade granite in the kitchen, along with an eight-foot live-edge Tiger Oak countertop, grace the interior. Barn doors grace the generously sized walk-in laundry room, and French doors open to the enclosed breezeway overlooking the pool and patio area. The outdoor space is just as captivating, featuring a fenced yard and an inviting built-in pool. Take pleasure in the elevated balcony, offering a picturesque spot for sunset views each evening. The primary suite on the main level encompasses a private office that holds potential for conversion into an expansive dressing room. The primary suite also showcases luxurious amenities such as heated tile floors, a jetted garden tub, and an adjoining sunroom. An additional guest room or in-law suite on the main floor includes an ensuite "wet bath." Further possibilities await in the attic space, which could accommodate a potential third-story addition. With almost 800 sq ft of space, the attic opens the door to myriad options—a "man cave," media room, crafts area, or even a music room. Ample storage solutions add to the versatility of this remarkable property. The highly esteemed Harrison Hills community is poised to make a lasting impression. Conveniently located near Simpsonville's shopping, dining, and easy access to 385.
